radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated to 10 mm and hyperenhancing, with surrounding soft tissue stranding, consistent with acute appendicitis. Most significant wall thickening of the appendix is seen near the base. There is also wall thickening at the base of the cecum. There is a 1.6 cm simple cyst in the lower pole of the left kidney. Additional hypodensity in the left kidney likely represents a simple cyst. There are multiple enlarged mesenteric lymph nodes in the right lower quadrant measuring up to 1.1 cm, likely reactive.
